00:46:07.160 --> 00:46:10.920
"I," said the thrush
as she sat on a bush.

765
00:46:11.480 --> 00:46:13.400
"I'll sing a song."

766
00:46:13.480 --> 00:46:15.360
"Who'll toll the bell?"

767
00:46:15.440 --> 00:46:18.800
"I," said the bull,
"because I can pull.

768
00:46:19.440 --> 00:46:21.080
I'll toll the bell."

769
00:46:21.160 --> 00:46:23.640
All the birds of the air

770
00:46:23.720 --> 00:46:26.600
fell a-sighing and a-sobbing

771
00:46:26.680 --> 00:46:29.400
when they heard the bell toll

772
00:46:29.480 --> 00:46:32.480
for poor Cock Robin!

773
00:46:39.520 --> 00:46:40.640
It's gonna be okay.

774
00:46:45.760 --> 00:46:48.000
All right. Okay, which one is she?

775
00:46:48.320 --> 00:46:49.560
The red one.

776
00:46:53.240 --> 00:46:54.320
- Bye.
- Go on.

777
00:47:05.200 --> 00:47:06.320
<i>Hallo, Johanna.</i>

778
00:47:59.360 --> 00:48:00.680
Hello. Hi.

779
00:48:08.440 --> 00:48:09.720
They're all in the chamber hall?

780
00:48:10.000 --> 00:48:11.000
Yes.

781
00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:13.040
No.

782
00:48:53.080 --> 00:48:54.080
Good morning.

783
00:48:55.640 --> 00:48:57.400
Oh, I'm sorry, Maestro.

784
00:48:58.000 --> 00:48:59.520
We weren't sure you were coming.

785
00:48:59.600 --> 00:49:02.120
We were told there might be
a scheduling conflict.

786
00:49:03.000 --> 00:49:04.560
Would you like me to take notes?

787
00:49:04.760 --> 00:49:05.840
No, thank you, Sebastian.

788
00:49:05.920 --> 00:49:07.040
That won't be necessary.

789
00:49:07.600 --> 00:49:09.080
Do we all have our rating sheets?

790
00:49:09.160 --> 00:49:10.360
We narrowed it down to three.

791
00:49:11.200 --> 00:49:13.200
So, unless anyone has
other business to discuss

792
00:49:13.280 --> 00:49:14.400
let's bring in number one.

793
00:50:29.200 --> 00:50:31.200
Goossens stands, sounds his A.

794
00:50:31.760 --> 00:50:38.000
And of course, Léon was rather famous
for his rather wide vibrato, huh?

795
00:50:38.680 --> 00:50:41.960
Beecham looks up and says,
"Gentlemen, take your pick."

796
00:50:44.480 --> 00:50:45.680
How's the writing going?

797
00:50:47.160 --> 00:50:49.440
I never know
how to answer that question.

798
00:50:49.520 --> 00:50:50.560
No.

799
00:50:50.920 --> 00:50:55.320
Makes it sound like a physical act.
Like, how's the shitting going?

800
00:50:57.000 --> 00:50:58.000
Okay.

801
00:50:58.320 --> 00:50:59.920
How's the thinking going?

802
00:51:00.000 --> 00:51:01.520
Yeah, not so well.

803
00:51:02.320 --> 00:51:04.760
I keep hearing something
and getting excited

804
00:51:04.840 --> 00:51:07.800
only to catch myself in pastiche.

805
00:51:09.600 --> 00:51:11.000
It's all pastiche.

806
00:51:11.960 --> 00:51:14.160
We all have the same musical grammar.

807
00:51:14.880 --> 00:51:16.640
Just look at Beethoven Five.

808
00:51:17.440 --> 00:51:20.200
The third movement's theme has
the same sequence of intervals

809
00:51:20.400 --> 00:51:23.560
as the opening theme of
the final movement of Mozart Forty.

810
00:51:23.880 --> 00:51:25.720
Th-that could've been a coincidence.

811
00:51:25.800 --> 00:51:27.680
No. Not in this case.

812
00:51:27.960 --> 00:51:30.000
If you examine
the sketchbooks he used

813
00:51:30.520 --> 00:51:34.320
29 bars of Mozart's finale appear.

814
00:51:34.520 --> 00:51:36.320
Copied out by Beethoven.

815
00:51:36.960 --> 00:51:40.200
Oh, my God. I find that
extremely depressing.

816
00:51:41.200 --> 00:51:44.040
I finished reading your manuscript.
It's very good, Lydia.

817
00:51:44.600 --> 00:51:46.240
One for the ages.

818
00:51:46.680 --> 00:51:48.320
And, I dare say, will be available

819
00:51:48.400 --> 00:51:49.920
long after my book
has been forgotten.

820
00:51:50.000 --> 00:51:51.200
Oh, yes, you're right.

821
00:51:51.480 --> 00:51:54.560
The entire first printing
will always be available.

822
00:51:54.960 --> 00:51:56.520
Too modest, as usual.

823
00:52:05.600 --> 00:52:06.760
Thank you, Andris.

824
00:52:08.320 --> 00:52:09.400
I'll cherish this.

825
00:52:09.920 --> 00:52:11.040
You may use it.

826
00:52:12.240 --> 00:52:14.000
A... a blurb for the covers.

827
00:52:15.440 --> 00:52:17.680
Oh, thank you.

828
00:52:18.280 --> 00:52:19.800
I'll send it to the publisher.

829
00:52:20.200 --> 00:52:21.480
Hopefully, there's still time.

830
00:52:22.160 --> 00:52:23.960
I'm proud to call you my pupil

831
00:52:24.600 --> 00:52:26.616
even though there was really
nothing I could teach you.

832
00:52:26.640 --> 00:52:27.880
Now, that's not true.

833
00:52:28.120 --> 00:52:30.520
I'd never have the position here
were it not for you.

834
00:52:31.160 --> 00:52:33.360
Then you'd be in London, New York.

835
00:52:33.800 --> 00:52:35.000
They're not Berlin.

836
00:52:36.600 --> 00:52:39.000
Besides, I'm not sure
what Sharon would do

837
00:52:39.080 --> 00:52:41.640
were we ever to leave.
She's so close with her family.

838
00:52:41.720 --> 00:52:44.520
Ah, yeah, the Goodnow sisters.

839
00:52:45.120 --> 00:52:47.440
I remember the elder one
being an absolute ball-breaker

840
00:52:47.520 --> 00:52:49.680
while she still held sway at DG.

841
00:52:50.520 --> 00:52:53.800
Heike is a woman of many opinions.

842
00:52:54.280 --> 00:52:55.320
And that voice.

843
00:52:55.400 --> 00:52:58.480
I mean, the signal-to-noise ratio,
it's unbearable.

844
00:52:59.240 --> 00:53:01.160
I've had to bolt-hole
at my old place in town

845
00:53:01.240 --> 00:53:02.600
to get any writing done.

846
00:53:03.480 --> 00:53:05.200
Schopenhauer measured
a man's intelligence

847
00:53:05.280 --> 00:53:07.360
against his sensitivity to noise.

848
00:53:08.280 --> 00:53:11.840
Didn't he once also throw
a woman down a flight of stairs

849
00:53:11.920 --> 00:53:12.960
who later sued him?

850
00:53:13.040 --> 00:53:14.040
Yes.

851
00:53:14.360 --> 00:53:17.400
Although, it's unclear
this private and personal failing

852
00:53:17.480 --> 00:53:19.200
is at all relevant to his work.

853
00:53:27.360 --> 00:53:28.360
You're late.

854
00:53:31.000 --> 00:53:32.256
- Here, give me your stick.
- Thank you.

855
00:53:32.280 --> 00:53:33.280
I've got it.

856
00:57:10.560 --> 00:57:11.560
Okay.

857
00:57:14.360 --> 00:57:19.000
(German)

858
00:57:19.080 --> 00:57:24.000
(German)

859
00:57:24.600 --> 00:57:25.600
Okay?

860
00:57:26.040 --> 00:57:27.480
But it's also...

861
00:57:28.120 --> 00:57:31.560
It's like we're hearing it
from a very, very great distance.

862
00:57:31.640 --> 00:57:32.640
So it's...

863
00:57:38.240 --> 00:57:39.920
Sorry. Is Harald nearby?

864
00:57:40.000 --> 00:57:41.880
(German)

865
00:57:41.960 --> 00:57:44.320
Harald? I was just wondering
if you might

866
00:57:44.600 --> 00:57:46.400
quickly rig something up for us?

867
00:58:16.640 --> 00:58:17.640
Good, good, good.

868
00:58:17.720 --> 00:58:19.240
(German) Harald?

869
00:58:19.680 --> 00:58:20.680
(German)

870
00:58:21.120 --> 00:58:23.440
We'll want the same backstage setup
for the live recording.

871
00:58:23.720 --> 00:58:25.200
One, two, one.

872
00:58:44.600 --> 00:58:51.520
(German)

873
00:58:52.000 --> 00:58:53.920
Okay? Looks great, but...

874
00:58:54.800 --> 00:58:56.760
we need to hear it. Okay? It's not...

875
00:59:00.280 --> 00:59:01.280
Hey.

876
00:59:01.960 --> 00:59:08.720
(German)

877
00:59:09.560 --> 00:59:10.560
Okay?

878
00:59:13.280 --> 00:59:14.280
(German)

879
00:59:24.520 --> 00:59:26.200
No. (German)

880
00:59:28.400 --> 00:59:29.800
It's... it's much too slow.

881
00:59:30.920 --> 00:59:32.680
(German)

882
00:59:33.800 --> 00:59:36.240
(German)

883
00:59:40.400 --> 00:59:41.400
Okay.

884
00:59:42.280 --> 00:59:43.480
Okay, tutti.

885
00:59:45.280 --> 00:59:46.680
(German)

886
00:59:47.800 --> 00:59:49.240
How are things feeling up here?

887
00:59:49.640 --> 00:59:51.320
- Fine, yeah.
- Yeah, actually great

888
00:59:51.400 --> 00:59:54.640
but it's a shame we don't
record this one direct-to-disk.

889
00:59:55.360 --> 00:59:56.920
It's criminal, is more like it.

890
00:59:58.480 --> 00:59:59.800
Will you shoot me the MP3s?

891
01:00:00.160 --> 01:00:02.040
Yeah, sure,
but don't you want WAV files?

892
01:00:02.120 --> 01:00:05.080
No, just think what people
will actually be streaming.

893
01:00:05.160 --> 01:00:06.160
What about video?

894
01:00:06.240 --> 01:00:08.080
Yes, yes. Stage left A camera.

895
01:00:08.160 --> 01:00:09.640
- Okay.
- All right. Thanks, guys.

896
01:00:09.720 --> 01:00:11.360
Okay. Bye. You're quite welcome.

897
01:00:11.440 --> 01:00:13.320
(German)

898
01:00:13.760 --> 01:00:15.000
- There?
- Yeah.

899
01:00:15.200 --> 01:00:16.200
You want us to come...

900
01:00:16.280 --> 01:00:17.856
- to come in stronger there?
- Okay, then yeah.

901
01:00:17.880 --> 01:00:21.000
Here, 'cause the reigning dynamic
is forte, which is not good.

902
01:00:21.920 --> 01:00:23.000
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

903
01:00:23.320 --> 01:00:25.600
Just one small thing, Maestro.

904
01:00:25.680 --> 01:00:27.320
During the scherzo

905
01:00:28.560 --> 01:00:31.400
th-th-the clarinet solo's
still a bit too loud.

906
01:00:31.480 --> 01:00:33.680
It should really be
an accompanying figure

907
01:00:33.760 --> 01:00:35.080
to the first violins.

908
01:00:36.240 --> 01:00:39.000
But apart from that,
I'd say we're in very good shape.

909
01:00:39.920 --> 01:00:41.120
Thank you, Sebastian.

910
01:00:41.760 --> 01:00:42.760
Thank you.

911
01:00:48.640 --> 01:00:49.880
Accurate assessment?

912
01:00:50.720 --> 01:00:51.800
I don't think so.

913
01:00:52.400 --> 01:00:55.080
The clarinet is marked piano,
and we are marked pianissimo.

914
01:00:55.160 --> 01:00:57.120
Sebastian likes to sit in the stalls

915
01:00:57.200 --> 01:01:00.280
but there's no problem
with the balance in the circle.

916
01:01:05.120 --> 01:01:06.680
Something a bit more playful.

917
01:01:12.280 --> 01:01:14.400
Oh, and here's something
Tanya and I did with Gustavo.

918
01:01:14.480 --> 01:01:15.536
I think it's very powerful.

919
01:01:15.560 --> 01:01:18.200
Yes, it's... it's really
wonderful work, Karl.

920
01:01:18.280 --> 01:01:22.120
I'm just wondering if we might try
something a little less considered.

921
01:01:25.400 --> 01:01:27.200
Something simple like this?

922
01:01:28.960 --> 01:01:31.120
I'm not sure
how you would want to light it.

923
01:01:31.480 --> 01:01:33.520
Have Harald dim
the houselights to half.

924
01:01:35.120 --> 01:01:37.120
Houselights down half, please.

925
01:01:41.920 --> 01:01:44.640
I mean, we could make it work, but
we'd have to bring in some lights.

926
01:01:49.200 --> 01:01:50.840
If we want to do something like this

927
01:01:51.680 --> 01:01:54.120
we'll have to bring the hot lights
next week, Tanya

928
01:01:54.200 --> 01:01:55.360
forget about the strobes.

929
01:01:58.240 --> 01:01:59.520
Thank you for waiting.

930
01:01:59.600 --> 01:02:00.800
Of course, Maestro.

931
01:02:01.040 --> 01:02:03.680
How are we feeling
about today's rehearsal?

932
01:02:04.040 --> 01:02:07.200
Well, Sebastian thinks
your solo in the scherzo

933
01:02:07.280 --> 01:02:09.000
is a bit loud.

934
01:02:09.920 --> 01:02:10.920
It's possible.

935
01:02:11.400 --> 01:02:12.520
I don't agree.

936
01:02:12.880 --> 01:02:16.000
Your dynamic marking is higher
than that of the first violin.

937
01:02:16.080 --> 01:02:17.200
Yes, that's true.

938
01:02:18.320 --> 01:02:21.680
Look. Sebastian's getting old, Knut.

939
01:02:22.600 --> 01:02:23.720
I'm rotating him out.

940
01:02:24.960 --> 01:02:26.120
You're the first to know.

941
01:02:30.080 --> 01:02:31.120
Well...

942
01:02:34.040 --> 01:02:36.880
then I will organize a caucus,
and we'll take a vote.

943
01:02:36.960 --> 01:02:38.560
No. No, you won't.

944
01:02:40.240 --> 01:02:41.800
A vote must be taken.

945
01:02:41.880 --> 01:02:44.360
I am familiar with
the electoral conclave.

946
01:02:44.760 --> 01:02:46.600
But the appointment
of the assistant conductor

947
01:02:46.680 --> 01:02:48.600
is entirely my decision.

948
01:02:50.440 --> 01:02:51.440
Yes.

949
01:02:51.680 --> 01:02:54.680
So, I can count on
your support with the others?

950
01:02:57.120 --> 01:02:58.160
Yes.

951
01:02:58.240 --> 01:02:59.240
Good.

952
01:02:59.440 --> 01:03:00.640
Who will you replace him with?

953
01:03:00.720 --> 01:03:02.520
Oh. I'm considering a few names

954
01:03:02.600 --> 01:03:05.320
but the main thing is
we proceed with this immediately.

955
01:03:05.760 --> 01:03:06.800
I understand.

956
01:03:07.920 --> 01:03:10.280
Maestro, the other players
would like to know

957
01:03:10.360 --> 01:03:11.920
if you have chosen
the companion piece.

958
01:03:15.080 --> 01:03:16.120
Okay. Thanks.

959
01:03:43.840 --> 01:03:45.560
- I...
- It's okay.

960
01:03:45.920 --> 01:03:46.920
Thanks.

961
01:04:12.080 --> 01:04:17.400
<i>Changing major to minor</i>

962
01:04:20.880 --> 01:04:22.520
I'm sorry, I knocked.

963
01:04:24.440 --> 01:04:27.120
I knew you wanted your keys back
as quickly as possible.

964
01:04:27.200 --> 01:04:28.240
Yes, thanks.

965
01:04:28.880 --> 01:04:31.000
- Did you use the company card?
- Yeah.

966
01:04:31.280 --> 01:04:32.760
We can use it for your...

967
01:04:33.080 --> 01:04:34.200
your taxi home.

968
01:04:38.840 --> 01:04:41.120
Yeah. It's all right. You can go.

969
01:04:44.120 --> 01:04:46.400
It wasn't just the keys.

970
01:04:49.600 --> 01:04:51.880
I... I need someone to hold me.

971
01:04:54.320 --> 01:04:56.200
This isn't the place, Francesca.

972
01:04:57.800 --> 01:05:00.320
You're... That's not about...

973
01:05:01.400 --> 01:05:02.400
I just...

974
01:05:03.640 --> 01:05:06.520
I just got this
from someone over at Accordion.

975
01:05:18.520 --> 01:05:19.680
Oh, no.

976
01:05:22.320 --> 01:05:23.600
When did this happen?

977
01:05:23.680 --> 01:05:25.320
Day before yesterday.

978
01:05:27.280 --> 01:05:30.400
That email she sent you,
it felt like she was already...

979
01:05:30.480 --> 01:05:32.520
Delete it. And the rest.

980
01:05:33.840 --> 01:05:36.120
There's no reason
to get caught up in any intrigue.

981
01:05:41.800 --> 01:05:42.800
Now, now.

982
01:05:44.880 --> 01:05:48.800
Come on. There's nothing
we could have done to stop her.

983
01:05:49.600 --> 01:05:51.040
She wasn't one of us.

984
01:06:07.000 --> 01:06:10.240
I can't stop thinking
about our trip up the Ucayali.

985
01:06:11.720 --> 01:06:13.520
- The three of us were so close.
- Yes.

986
01:06:13.600 --> 01:06:16.240
But that was before
she started making demands.

987
01:06:18.120 --> 01:06:22.480
No. There was just something
not quite right about her.

988
01:06:23.320 --> 01:06:25.160
She had so much promise.

989
01:06:25.920 --> 01:06:27.000
She did.

990
01:06:27.360 --> 01:06:28.400
Yes.

991
01:06:29.320 --> 01:06:30.880
Almost as much as you.

992
01:06:35.640 --> 01:06:37.880
Now, we have to forget about her.

993
01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:43.160
You understand?

994
01:06:48.600 --> 01:06:49.600
Right?

995
01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:54.360
- I'm sorry.
- No.

996
01:06:54.440 --> 01:06:55.640
I know you're working.

997
01:06:57.120 --> 01:06:58.120
Your...

998
01:06:58.640 --> 01:07:00.800
Your keys are on the kitchen table.

999
01:08:03.120 --> 01:08:04.720
She went straight to sleep.

1000
01:08:07.720 --> 01:08:09.480
Didn't even have to hold her foot.

1001
01:08:14.360 --> 01:08:17.120
And she came home
in a much better mood.

1002
01:08:17.200 --> 01:08:18.680
Oh, attagirl.

1003
01:08:28.640 --> 01:08:30.360
Met the new cellist today.

1004
01:08:30.440 --> 01:08:32.360
Oh, what was that like?

1005
01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:34.680
Olga Metkina.

1006
01:08:35.200 --> 01:08:36.200
Russian.

1007
01:08:36.960 --> 01:08:37.960
Strong player.

1008
01:08:38.760 --> 01:08:39.760
Good.

1009
01:08:41.440 --> 01:08:43.560
Her facial posture is a bit much.

1010
01:08:44.320 --> 01:08:45.360
How so?

1011
01:08:45.720 --> 01:08:49.200
Her legato. Looks like
she's on the verge of climaxing.

1012
01:08:53.640 --> 01:08:54.800
She is young.

1013
01:08:55.920 --> 01:08:57.120
So you've met her.

1014
01:08:59.240 --> 01:09:00.240
No, no.

1015
01:09:01.480 --> 01:09:03.240
Francesca mentioned something.

1016
01:09:03.320 --> 01:09:05.120
I think she's arranging
a welcome lunch.

1017
01:09:08.200 --> 01:09:09.800
You may want to hold off on that.

1018
01:09:11.120 --> 01:09:12.800
Her invitation is conditional.

1019
01:09:16.600 --> 01:09:18.080
You have reservations?

1020
01:09:18.920 --> 01:09:19.920
No.

1021
01:09:20.840 --> 01:09:21.920
Not really.

1022
01:09:23.400 --> 01:09:24.880
We need to see if she fits in.

1023
01:09:29.400 --> 01:09:30.680
Did you take your pill?

1024
01:09:32.640 --> 01:09:33.680
No.

1025
01:09:35.200 --> 01:09:36.800
Thank you for reminding me.

1026
01:11:01.440 --> 01:11:03.240
How was Johanna yesterday?

1027
01:11:03.680 --> 01:11:05.720
She stays away now.

1028
01:11:05.800 --> 01:11:08.000
Good. You let me know
if that changes.

1029
01:11:11.720 --> 01:11:14.680
Petra, last night, you weren't,
by any chance, in my study?

1030
01:11:16.080 --> 01:11:17.200
No, Lydia.

1031
01:11:17.280 --> 01:11:19.880
Because you do know you're not
supposed to be in there without me.

1032
01:11:19.920 --> 01:11:21.040
I know.

1033
01:11:23.400 --> 01:11:24.440
That's right.

1034
01:11:59.760 --> 01:12:02.320
It's not so simple.
It's got... it's got to be messier.

1035
01:12:02.400 --> 01:12:04.640
Moment. It's...

1036
01:12:05.040 --> 01:12:06.040
(German)

1037
01:12:06.760 --> 01:12:07.760
Okay?

1038
01:12:07.880 --> 01:12:15.880
(German)

1039
01:12:16.200 --> 01:12:18.200
A lot of pressure. Okay?

1040
01:12:18.560 --> 01:12:21.160
Forget Visconti.

1041
01:12:21.440 --> 01:12:24.000
Okay? It's so familiar
to everyone here.

1042
01:12:24.080 --> 01:12:26.880
It really doesn't help you
to know this piece so well. Okay.

1043
01:12:28.200 --> 01:12:29.200
Same place.

1044
01:12:42.600 --> 01:12:44.320
Just a little crescendo...

1045
01:12:45.360 --> 01:12:47.120
now let the third come through.

1046
01:12:57.920 --> 01:12:58.920
Please.

1047
01:12:59.520 --> 01:13:01.480
Please, please, please.

1048
01:13:01.560 --> 01:13:03.080
You must watch.

1049
01:13:04.680 --> 01:13:06.720
It's completely free here.

1050
01:13:07.680 --> 01:13:08.680
Okay?

1051
01:13:09.600 --> 01:13:13.600
It's got to be like just one person
singing their heart out.

1052
01:13:15.880 --> 01:13:16.880
And...

1053
01:13:18.400 --> 01:13:20.080
you're playing like an...

1054
01:13:20.480 --> 01:13:21.480
exercise.

1055
01:13:24.280 --> 01:13:25.280
Okay.

1056
01:13:25.360 --> 01:13:28.640
Once again
from the top of the Adagietto.

1057
01:13:33.720 --> 01:13:34.720
Okay.

1058
01:13:38.200 --> 01:13:39.200
Maestro.

1059
01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:42.520
What a surprise.
I was just having a spot of lunch.

1060
01:13:42.600 --> 01:13:44.160
C-Can I offer you anything?

1061
01:13:44.480 --> 01:13:45.480
No, thank you.

1062
01:13:45.560 --> 01:13:48.200
- Well, some tea, perhaps?
- No, thank you, Sebastian.

1063
01:13:49.120 --> 01:13:53.320
You know, I forget sometimes just how
impressive your collection is here.

1064
01:13:53.600 --> 01:13:55.120
Is that Kalinnikov?

1065
01:13:55.720 --> 01:13:56.760
Yes.

1066
01:13:57.240 --> 01:13:59.000
Isn't he marvelous?

1067
01:14:00.200 --> 01:14:01.640
He belongs in a museum.

1068
01:14:02.440 --> 01:14:06.880
I rescued him for a hundred rubles
from a Kyiv street fair back in '90.

1069
01:14:07.320 --> 01:14:08.720
Right after the Wall came down.

1070
01:14:09.520 --> 01:14:11.280
That must really have been something.

1071
01:14:11.360 --> 01:14:14.120
Oh, incredible
to have lived through it.

1072
01:14:14.480 --> 01:14:16.640
I'd only just arrived here
with Andris

1073
01:14:16.720 --> 01:14:19.600
and suddenly
the impossible was possible.

1074
01:14:19.840 --> 01:14:20.840
Yeah.

1075
01:14:22.880 --> 01:14:25.080
I'd like to talk about that.

1076
01:14:25.280 --> 01:14:27.000
- The reunification?
- No, no.

1077
01:14:27.080 --> 01:14:28.240
But please, sit down.

1078
01:14:28.920 --> 01:14:34.880
No, about the possibility of you
fronting a subscription orchestra.

1079
01:14:35.520 --> 01:14:36.840
But I already do.

1080
01:14:36.920 --> 01:14:39.000
Yes, but not as Kapellmeister.

1081
01:14:40.800 --> 01:14:43.400
If not now, then when, Sebastian?

1082
01:14:45.200 --> 01:14:46.680
You mean leave Berlin?

1083
01:14:46.880 --> 01:14:49.200
Well, rotate somewhere, yes.

1084
01:14:49.880 --> 01:14:51.200
But this is my home.

1085
01:14:52.080 --> 01:14:54.560
Our only home is the podium.

1086
01:14:55.160 --> 01:14:59.200
We all live out of a suitcase.
You know that as well as anyone.

1087
01:15:05.480 --> 01:15:06.680
Just think about it.

1088
01:15:08.280 --> 01:15:09.280
Take your time.

1089
01:15:10.640 --> 01:15:13.040
It's not something
we need to decide now.

1090
01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:17.480
It's the girl, isn't it?

1091
01:15:17.720 --> 01:15:18.800
I'm sorry, what girl?

1092
01:15:19.960 --> 01:15:21.200
You're not asking.

1093
01:15:21.680 --> 01:15:22.760
You're telling.

1094
01:15:23.640 --> 01:15:27.720
I knew as soon as she showed up
that my days here were numbered.

1095
01:15:27.960 --> 01:15:29.880
Andris told me not to worry, but...

1096
01:15:30.400 --> 01:15:31.400
I knew.

1097
01:15:32.160 --> 01:15:35.600
I'm sure I don't know
what you're talking about.

1098
01:15:35.680 --> 01:15:36.920
Oh, please.

1099
01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:40.920
Just because nobody dares breathe it.
We know the things you do.

1100
01:15:41.080 --> 01:15:43.320
The little favors you grant.

1101
01:15:43.880 --> 01:15:44.880
I'm...

1102
01:15:45.080 --> 01:15:47.880
I really don't know
what to say, Sebastian.

1103
01:15:48.480 --> 01:15:51.840
I mean, you of all people
have the temerity

1104
01:15:51.920 --> 01:15:53.360
- to question my integrity?
- No, no.

1105
01:15:53.400 --> 01:15:54.920
I'm... I'm sorry, Maestro.

1106
01:15:55.000 --> 01:15:56.616
- I don't know what I'm saying.
- No, no, no, it's clear

1107
01:15:56.640 --> 01:15:58.400
you know exactly what you're saying.

1108
01:15:58.960 --> 01:16:00.736
I mean, if that's how
you really feel about me

1109
01:16:00.760 --> 01:16:03.680
then wouldn't you say that staying is
entirely out of the question?

1110
01:16:03.760 --> 01:16:05.840
No, no, please, Maestro.
Please forgive me.

1111
01:16:05.920 --> 01:16:06.920
For what?

1112
01:16:07.000 --> 01:16:10.520
Your obsequiousness,
your hypocrisy, your misogamy?

1113
01:16:10.600 --> 01:16:11.680
I'm not a misogynist!

1114
01:16:11.760 --> 01:16:13.000
Misogamy.

1115
01:16:13.520 --> 01:16:15.240
It's a hatred of marriage.

1116
01:16:17.440 --> 01:16:20.200
Andris is still very much married.

1117
01:16:21.360 --> 01:16:25.200
And you occupy an apartment
on the same floor, don't you?

1118
01:16:26.480 --> 01:16:29.000
I just don't like what he's implying.

1119
01:16:30.280 --> 01:16:32.600
It could lead
to more than Chinese whispers.

1120
01:16:33.120 --> 01:16:34.120
I know.

1121
01:16:34.880 --> 01:16:37.880
We barely survived Der Spiegel
when you and I came out together.

1122
01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:43.720
But with Francesca,
no one could point their finger.

1123
01:16:44.400 --> 01:16:46.600
It's not like
you two are in a relationship.

1124
01:16:46.680 --> 01:16:47.680
Yeah, that's true.

1125
01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:50.280
I just... Turns my stomach to think

1126
01:16:50.360 --> 01:16:52.520
the old robot will be right
about something.

1127
01:16:54.520 --> 01:16:56.920
He's probably already run to Andris.

1128
01:16:58.360 --> 01:16:59.360
Well

1129
01:17:00.160 --> 01:17:03.200
is there someone other than Francesca
you feel is more qualified?

1130
01:17:06.560 --> 01:17:08.600
There are others equal to the task.

1131
01:17:13.480 --> 01:17:15.120
Maybe wait to decide.

1132
01:17:24.560 --> 01:17:26.160
Where are we at with DG?

1133
01:17:26.240 --> 01:17:29.320
I spoke to an assistant
in Boyd Muir's office

1134
01:17:29.400 --> 01:17:33.920
who said they weren't sure why
they decided on a digital-only set

1135
01:17:34.000 --> 01:17:36.000
what the criteria were.

1136
01:17:36.440 --> 01:17:39.240
But I do know they just did
a full-vinyl pressing for Long Yu.

1137
01:17:39.320 --> 01:17:40.560
Of course they did.

1138
01:17:40.920 --> 01:17:42.520
The Chinese market's incredible.

1139
01:17:43.160 --> 01:17:44.960
All right. Gloves off.

1140
01:17:45.040 --> 01:17:46.400
I'm going straight to Lucian.

1141
01:17:46.720 --> 01:17:49.720
Maybe he needs to be reminded of
his Annenberg Inclusion Initiative.

1142
01:17:51.120 --> 01:17:52.800
You've got
his contact details, right?

1143
01:17:53.680 --> 01:17:55.320
I'll send it to you right now.

1144
01:17:57.520 --> 01:17:59.800
My machine's misbehaving again.

1145
01:18:00.760 --> 01:18:02.440
I've already spoken to IT.

1146
01:18:02.520 --> 01:18:04.160
Just here... let me borrow yours.

1147
01:18:11.440 --> 01:18:12.440
Thank you.

1148
01:18:16.200 --> 01:18:17.240
Where's the matcha?

1149
01:19:00.680 --> 01:19:02.640
I wasn't sure where you were.

1150
01:19:02.920 --> 01:19:04.320
Was working out a kink.

1151
01:19:04.920 --> 01:19:06.280
The... the matcha's cold.

1152
01:19:06.360 --> 01:19:07.936
- I... I'll get another.
- It's all right. I don't need it.

1153
01:19:07.960 --> 01:19:09.640
Let's just keep working.

1154
01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:19.200
Francesca, you did as I asked

1155
01:19:19.280 --> 01:19:23.400
and deleted any and all
correspondence with Krista, correct?

1156
01:19:27.400 --> 01:19:28.520
I'm not sure.

1157
01:19:29.800 --> 01:19:32.800
I'm... I'm not sure.
I'll double-check.

1158
01:19:40.520 --> 01:19:42.400
You know, Sebastian's leaving us

1159
01:19:43.360 --> 01:19:48.320
and I wondered if you might compile
a list of suitable replacements.

1160
01:19:54.040 --> 01:19:55.920
Of course, feel free
to add your own name.

1161
01:19:59.400 --> 01:20:00.400
Thank you.

1162
01:20:03.160 --> 01:20:06.320
Oh, your... your lunch
with the new cellist.

1163
01:20:06.680 --> 01:20:07.680
Oh.

1164
01:20:07.920 --> 01:20:10.680
Meant to have you reschedule that
'til after the orchestra votes.

1165
01:20:10.880 --> 01:20:12.360
I'll text her now.

1166
01:20:14.520 --> 01:20:15.520
No, wait.

1167
01:20:16.400 --> 01:20:18.040
Might as well see what she's made of.

1168
01:20:27.560 --> 01:20:28.640
This food.

1169
01:20:31.080 --> 01:20:33.520
The cucumber salad's very good.

1170
01:20:35.320 --> 01:20:38.320
It's kind of the only real option
in this place if you're vegetarian.

1171
01:20:39.600 --> 01:20:40.680
Do you eat fish?

1172
01:20:40.760 --> 01:20:41.760
Not really.

1173
01:20:45.360 --> 01:20:47.520
You know, we can go somewhere else.

1174
01:20:47.960 --> 01:20:49.680
L-Like the Store Kitchen.

1175
01:20:49.760 --> 01:20:52.800
I mean, it's... it's kind
of a silly tradition really

1176
01:20:52.880 --> 01:20:56.800
that new members are brought here
to sup with the ghosts of the past.

1177
01:20:57.960 --> 01:21:01.800
I mean, at some point, everyone
from... from Napoleon to Beethoven

1178
01:21:01.880 --> 01:21:04.000
tucked in for a meal
at one of these tables.

1179
01:21:04.080 --> 01:21:06.000
Yes, and Clara Zetkin.

1180
01:21:06.960 --> 01:21:08.320
I wonder which one.

1181
01:21:08.480 --> 01:21:11.000
Who's that? It's a musician?

1182
01:21:11.080 --> 01:21:13.000
No. She helped found

1183
01:21:13.080 --> 01:21:15.800
Social Democratic
women's movement in Germany

1184
01:21:15.880 --> 01:21:18.960
and KPD until Hitler came to power

1185
01:21:19.040 --> 01:21:21.000
and she was exiled to Soviet Union.

1186
01:21:21.720 --> 01:21:23.720
- Clara Zetkin?
- Yes.

1187
01:21:24.360 --> 01:21:25.360
Every March 8th

1188
01:21:25.440 --> 01:21:28.800
we place flowers at her plaque
in Kremlin Wall Necropolis.

1189
01:21:29.320 --> 01:21:30.320
Her birthday?

1190
01:21:30.880 --> 01:21:33.400
No, International Women's Day.

1191
01:21:36.200 --> 01:21:37.320
Are you ready, Maestro?

1192
01:21:38.760 --> 01:21:42.400
- Yes...
- Yes, first shashlik, then veal.

1193
01:21:43.680 --> 01:21:44.680
For you?

1194
01:21:45.400 --> 01:21:47.360
- Cucumber salad. Thank you.
- Good choice.

1195
01:21:50.480 --> 01:21:51.520
Some more bread?

1196
01:21:59.520 --> 01:22:00.920
It's good. Would you like a bite?

1197
01:22:01.520 --> 01:22:02.520
Oh, no.

1198
01:22:02.680 --> 01:22:03.760
No. Thank you.

1199
01:22:05.520 --> 01:22:07.120
Have you lived in Berlin long?

1200
01:22:07.440 --> 01:22:08.680
No, not at all.

1201
01:22:09.080 --> 01:22:12.560
I have friends in Wicker I visit
until I know decision of orchestra.

1202
01:22:14.040 --> 01:22:15.480
Simonov will hold your place?

1203
01:22:15.960 --> 01:22:17.960
Yes, I think so. He is my uncle.

1204
01:22:19.720 --> 01:22:20.720
Oh.

1205
01:22:20.800 --> 01:22:23.640
But my dream has always been
to play with Berlin.

1206
01:22:23.720 --> 01:22:24.800
Oh, me, too.

1207
01:22:26.200 --> 01:22:27.400
There's nowhere like it.

1208
01:22:31.680 --> 01:22:34.200
I imagine Rostropovich is
a hero of yours.

1209
01:22:35.840 --> 01:22:37.520
Well, of course, he was great.

1210
01:22:38.080 --> 01:22:40.040
We study him at Moscow Conservatory

1211
01:22:40.120 --> 01:22:44.000
but growing up, my favorite
is Jacqueline du Pré.

1212
01:22:44.320 --> 01:22:45.920
She made me want to play cello.

1213
01:22:47.200 --> 01:22:48.200
Which record was it?

1214
01:22:48.280 --> 01:22:50.120
Not record. YouTube.

1215
01:22:50.600 --> 01:22:51.920
Elgar Concerto.

1216
01:22:54.240 --> 01:22:55.320
Oh, of course.

1217
01:22:55.400 --> 01:22:57.360
With Barenboim conducting
the London Phil.

1218
01:22:58.120 --> 01:23:00.000
I don't know who was conducting.

1219
01:23:01.080 --> 01:23:03.000
But she did something to me.

1220
01:23:03.680 --> 01:23:07.000
That's when I decide to learn piece
and play it with youth orchestra.

1221
01:23:07.880 --> 01:23:09.640
Quite a challenge. How old were you?

1222
01:23:09.720 --> 01:23:10.720
Thirteen.

1223
01:23:12.720 --> 01:23:13.720
Wow.

1224
01:23:14.560 --> 01:23:15.680
I'd love to hear it.

1225
01:23:16.320 --> 01:23:18.400
They make video. I will text to you.

1226
01:26:19.360 --> 01:26:20.480
Beautiful.

1227
01:26:24.280 --> 01:26:25.280
Very nice indeed.

1228
01:26:25.920 --> 01:26:27.200
Let's leave it here.

1229
01:26:27.760 --> 01:26:30.480
Tomorrow we'll begin
with the Rondo-Finale.

1230
01:26:31.240 --> 01:26:33.320
Now, just before we break

1231
01:26:33.400 --> 01:26:38.320
I know many of you are wondering
what the companion piece will be.

1232
01:26:38.400 --> 01:26:40.320
And I have been thinking
quite a bit about it

1233
01:26:40.800 --> 01:26:42.600
and was wondering
if we could just take

1234
01:26:42.680 --> 01:26:45.800
an informal poll about
possibly pairing the Five

1235
01:26:46.360 --> 01:26:48.520
with Elgar's Cello Concerto.

1236
01:27:10.320 --> 01:27:11.320
Wonderful.

1237
01:27:11.600 --> 01:27:12.600
Elgar it is.

1238
01:27:13.760 --> 01:27:17.440
Oh, and... given what
we've all been through

1239
01:27:18.200 --> 01:27:19.600
what we're still going through

1240
01:27:20.000 --> 01:27:23.880
and we're finally back together
as a family, I... I...

1241
01:27:25.480 --> 01:27:29.960
I feel that maybe the soloist should
come from within our own ranks.

1242
01:27:30.520 --> 01:27:31.520
Yeah.

1243
01:27:32.400 --> 01:27:33.400
Good.

1244
01:27:33.680 --> 01:27:34.880
Okay, good. Just... Sorry.

1245
01:27:35.600 --> 01:27:36.720
One more question.

1246
01:27:36.800 --> 01:27:38.720
And this really is
just for you, Gosia.

1247
01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:40.000
I mean...

1248
01:27:40.560 --> 01:27:44.920
as a practical matter, I mean,
this would normally fall to you.

1249
01:27:45.320 --> 01:27:47.720
But given how much is gonna be
asked of you with the Mahler

1250
01:27:47.800 --> 01:27:49.560
I... I wondered
if you'd be at all bothered

1251
01:27:49.640 --> 01:27:51.600
if we were to hold auditions?

1252
01:28:00.680 --> 01:28:03.480
Well, that's a bit unorthodox.

1253
01:28:06.880 --> 01:28:09.320
But, in theory, I have no objection.

1254
01:28:09.880 --> 01:28:11.200
My only hesitation will depend

1255
01:28:11.280 --> 01:28:12.776
on when these auditions
might take place.

1256
01:28:12.800 --> 01:28:15.680
I wouldn't want them in any way
to interfere with our sectionals.

1257
01:28:15.760 --> 01:28:17.160
No, no. That's a good point.

1258
01:28:17.240 --> 01:28:18.600
I mean, it's gonna have to be a...

1259
01:28:19.160 --> 01:28:20.400
It's gonna have to be a sprint.

1260
01:28:23.280 --> 01:28:24.440
How about Monday?

1261
01:28:28.840 --> 01:28:29.840
All right.

1262
01:28:34.040 --> 01:28:37.880
Okay, good. Knut, would you assemble
a quorum for Monday?

1263
01:28:52.200 --> 01:28:53.720
Let me see what she says.

1264
01:28:54.400 --> 01:28:55.960
Okay, I got... I gotta go.

1265
01:28:57.600 --> 01:28:58.760
Britta, hi.

1266
01:28:59.040 --> 01:29:00.040
Lydia.

1267
01:29:00.320 --> 01:29:01.760
Just caught the end.

1268
01:29:02.160 --> 01:29:03.896
What'd you think?
How's it... how's it sounding?

1269
01:29:03.920 --> 01:29:05.400
Oh, it's fantastic.

1270
01:29:06.200 --> 01:29:08.320
I can't wait
until the live recording.

1271
01:29:08.400 --> 01:29:09.680
Yes, well.

1272
01:29:10.040 --> 01:29:11.920
I'll be happy when it's over.

1273
01:29:12.160 --> 01:29:13.400
It's always that way.

1274
01:29:14.200 --> 01:29:16.880
I know you're busy,
and I don't want to add to your load

1275
01:29:17.160 --> 01:29:18.160
but...

1276
01:29:19.200 --> 01:29:20.800
Andris Davis called.

1277
01:29:21.360 --> 01:29:24.640
Look, he's upset
I'm rotating Sebastian.

1278
01:29:24.720 --> 01:29:25.720
No... no.

1279
01:29:25.800 --> 01:29:26.960
Something else.

1280
01:29:27.040 --> 01:29:28.256
But you will please let Laura know

1281
01:29:28.280 --> 01:29:29.696
as soon as you have chosen
his replacement

1282
01:29:29.720 --> 01:29:30.976
so she can prepare a press release.

1283
01:29:31.000 --> 01:29:32.200
Yeah, of course.

1284
01:29:33.080 --> 01:29:34.120
So what did he want?

1285
01:29:34.280 --> 01:29:36.480
To complain about
the punctuality of a driver

1286
01:29:36.560 --> 01:29:38.880
he seems to believe
the board supplies him with.

1287
01:29:39.400 --> 01:29:41.200
Do you know anything about this?

1288
01:29:41.480 --> 01:29:42.480
Yes.

1289
01:29:43.120 --> 01:29:45.120
No, it's just... it's just
something I pay for.

1290
01:29:45.720 --> 01:29:47.640
Then why does he believe
it's the board?

1291
01:29:48.400 --> 01:29:50.120
Because he needs to believe that.

1292
01:29:51.240 --> 01:29:52.520
H-He needs to b...

1293
01:29:53.160 --> 01:29:55.120
needs to believe
he hasn't been forgotten, Britta.

1294
01:29:55.720 --> 01:29:58.320
The academy
has von Karajan's name on it

1295
01:29:58.400 --> 01:30:00.760
and there are love shrines
to Abbado all over this place.

1296
01:30:00.840 --> 01:30:04.920
But the name of Davis,
it's essentially nowhere to be seen.

1297
01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:06.000
All right.

1298
01:30:06.560 --> 01:30:09.520
Then perhaps Francesca could
have a word with the driver.

1299
01:30:10.000 --> 01:30:11.000
Of course.

1300
01:30:12.320 --> 01:30:13.520
One other thing.

1301
01:30:14.000 --> 01:30:15.200
It's unpleasant.

1302
01:30:15.960 --> 01:30:17.080
Oh, is it?

1303
01:30:17.160 --> 01:30:18.640
Operational shortfall?

1304
01:30:19.320 --> 01:30:21.520
Must I take Mrs. Sewing out
to drinks again?

1305
01:30:21.600 --> 01:30:23.440
No, no, no, nothing to do
with the orchestra.

1306
01:30:23.520 --> 01:30:25.680
Do you remember
an Accordion Academy fellow

1307
01:30:25.760 --> 01:30:27.320
named Krista Taylor?

1308
01:30:30.840 --> 01:30:32.960
Yes. Why?

1309
01:30:33.040 --> 01:30:35.000
Apparently, she committed suicide.

1310
01:30:35.880 --> 01:30:37.640
Oh, God. Poor thing.

1311
01:30:38.680 --> 01:30:39.920
Her parents mu...

1312
01:30:41.480 --> 01:30:42.800
Wait, sorry, I'm...

1313
01:30:43.560 --> 01:30:44.560
I'm confused, Britta.

1314
01:30:44.640 --> 01:30:46.400
Why... why were you put
in the position

1315
01:30:46.480 --> 01:30:47.720
to deliver this terrible news?

1316
01:30:47.800 --> 01:30:49.720
Why didn't Accordion
contact me directly?

1317
01:30:49.920 --> 01:30:51.480
It's delicate, Lydia.

1318
01:30:51.720 --> 01:30:53.096
Mr. Kaplan thought it might be best

1319
01:30:53.120 --> 01:30:56.320
if you contacted a lawyer before
speaking with anyone at Accordion.

1320
01:30:57.160 --> 01:31:00.000
Well, presumably, that
anyone includes Eliot himself.

1321
01:31:02.080 --> 01:31:04.320
I'm... I'm sorry, why... why
would I need to do that?

1322
01:31:05.440 --> 01:31:09.000
Apparently, some accusations
have been made.

1323
01:31:11.240 --> 01:31:13.280
Accusations?
What kind of accusations?

1324
01:31:13.360 --> 01:31:14.400
He didn't say.

1325
01:31:14.840 --> 01:31:16.720
But they were brought
to Accordion's counsel.

1326
01:31:17.120 --> 01:31:19.760
Mr. Kaplan said he's certain
nothing will come of it

1327
01:31:19.840 --> 01:31:21.800
but one can't be too careful.

1328
01:31:40.160 --> 01:31:42.480
I'm sorry about the hour.
It's Lydia Tár calling.

1329
01:31:42.560 --> 01:31:44.720
I need to speak
to Mr. Singer immediately.

1330
01:31:45.720 --> 01:31:46.720
Yes.

1331
01:31:46.960 --> 01:31:48.120
Yes, it's urgent.

1332
01:32:16.840 --> 01:32:17.840
Tired?

1333
01:32:22.080 --> 01:32:23.520
Sleep's elusive.

1334
01:32:24.720 --> 01:32:26.920
I was the same
before a recording date.

1335
01:32:28.880 --> 01:32:29.880
Lydia...

1336
01:32:30.840 --> 01:32:33.800
are... are you absolutely certain
about Sebastian?

1337
01:32:36.600 --> 01:32:38.000
Who will you replace him with?

1338
01:32:39.320 --> 01:32:40.920
Possibly Andrew Crust.

1339
01:32:42.440 --> 01:32:45.120
He's been assisting
Otto Tausk at the VSO.

1340
01:32:45.720 --> 01:32:46.760
Not the girl?

1341
01:32:56.800 --> 01:32:57.840
Andris...

1342
01:33:01.680 --> 01:33:07.320
have you ever had an issue
with a... a student or colleague

1343
01:33:07.400 --> 01:33:09.440
where that person may
have misinterpreted your...

1344
01:33:09.520 --> 01:33:10.576
- intention?
- Has someone been complaining

1345
01:33:10.600 --> 01:33:11.656
- about me?
- No, no, no, of course not.

1346
01:33:11.680 --> 01:33:13.576
Because at this point,
they've missed their chance.

1347
01:33:13.600 --> 01:33:15.800
- I'm out of the game.
- Yes, yes, I know, I know.

1348
01:33:15.880 --> 01:33:16.880
Course you are.

1349
01:33:17.520 --> 01:33:21.320
Thank God I was never pulled
from the podium like Jimmy Levine.

1350
01:33:21.960 --> 01:33:24.040
Or hunted like Charles Dutoit.

1351
01:33:24.960 --> 01:33:26.920
I take it you're asking for a reason.

1352
01:33:27.840 --> 01:33:30.360
Well, there's just been
so much of this sort of thing

1353
01:33:30.440 --> 01:33:31.520
in the news lately.

1354
01:33:31.800 --> 01:33:34.520
Well, nowadays, to be accused
is the same as being guilty.

1355
01:33:35.720 --> 01:33:39.880
But I suppose that was also the case
all those years ago with Furtwängler.

1356
01:33:40.600 --> 01:33:42.400
A bit with Karajan, too.

1357
01:33:46.200 --> 01:33:47.680
Who was the better conductor?

1358
01:33:49.440 --> 01:33:51.120
I never played under Furtwängler.

1359
01:33:51.880 --> 01:33:54.800
Yeah, when I first arrived here,
the older members had...

1360
01:33:55.840 --> 01:33:57.400
hushed opinions.

1361
01:33:57.920 --> 01:34:01.000
At the same time,
they wanted to leave that era behind.

1362
01:34:01.080 --> 01:34:03.000
- What, the war?
- No, postwar.

1363
01:34:03.480 --> 01:34:05.000
Denazification.

1364
01:34:05.720 --> 01:34:09.400
Someone pointed a finger at you,
process started all over again.

1365
01:34:09.840 --> 01:34:11.800
Furtwängler never joined the Party.

1366
01:34:11.880 --> 01:34:15.040
Refused to give the salute or
to conduct the <i>Horst Wessel Lied.</i>

1367
01:34:15.640 --> 01:34:17.720
Or to sign his letters,
"Heil, Hitler."

1368
01:34:18.040 --> 01:34:19.400
Even those he wrote to Hitler.

1369
01:34:20.920 --> 01:34:24.000
But he was obliged to be denazified.

1370
01:34:25.320 --> 01:34:27.320
Until then, he was semi-retired

1371
01:34:28.360 --> 01:34:29.880
playing corpses.

1372
01:34:31.160 --> 01:34:32.880
Playing corpses?

1373
01:34:33.480 --> 01:34:35.840
Secretly performing in a graveyard.

1374
01:34:38.240 --> 01:34:40.400
You're not equating
sexual impropriety

1375
01:34:40.480 --> 01:34:42.000
with being an accused Nazi?

1376
01:34:43.200 --> 01:34:44.720
Either way, you had to be ready.

1377
01:34:45.000 --> 01:34:46.120
For years, I made sure

1378
01:34:46.200 --> 01:34:49.320
all the hangers in my closet
were facing the same direction.

1379
01:35:00.040 --> 01:35:02.400
How many are auditioning on Monday?

1380
01:35:06.800 --> 01:35:07.920
No one.

1381
01:35:08.800 --> 01:35:09.800
No one?

1382
01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:13.200
Maybe Martin.

1383
01:35:15.000 --> 01:35:16.480
He's never gotten along with Gosia.

1384
01:35:16.560 --> 01:35:18.680
He would love
to sit downstage for once.

1385
01:35:20.200 --> 01:35:21.200
Well...

1386
01:35:22.800 --> 01:35:24.400
he's still gonna have to audition.

1387
01:35:26.920 --> 01:35:27.920
Of course.

1388
01:35:28.960 --> 01:35:30.360
Have to follow the rules.

1389
01:35:33.200 --> 01:35:35.240
Aren't we being
a bit formal, Francesca?

1390
01:35:35.320 --> 01:35:37.640
From what I understand,
there's only one player, right?

1391
01:35:37.720 --> 01:35:39.520
No, Maestro, there are two.

1392
01:36:40.160 --> 01:36:41.480
Well, it's unanimous.

1393
01:36:41.800 --> 01:36:42.800
Number two.

1394
01:36:44.600 --> 01:36:45.680
And we have a problem.

1395
01:36:45.960 --> 01:36:48.960
She's not officially been invited
to become a member of the orchestra.

1396
01:36:50.400 --> 01:36:53.040
Well, she wouldn't need
to be to solo for us.

1397
01:36:53.920 --> 01:36:55.920
I believe the criteria
of the audition

1398
01:36:56.000 --> 01:36:58.160
was all section members?

1399
01:36:59.040 --> 01:37:00.800
- Then her audition gets thrown out.
- No.

1400
01:37:01.040 --> 01:37:03.000
Francesca, please ask Martin
to come back in

1401
01:37:03.080 --> 01:37:04.200
so we can give him the news.

1402
01:37:04.560 --> 01:37:06.200
Wait. Gosia, let's talk.

1403
01:37:09.800 --> 01:37:10.800
Shit!

1404
01:37:13.160 --> 01:37:14.160
Yeah!

1405
01:37:17.240 --> 01:37:19.760
I'll confirm
solo rehearsal dates with her.

1406
01:37:20.080 --> 01:37:21.080
Thank you.

1407
01:37:22.120 --> 01:37:23.120
Have a seat.

1408
01:37:28.760 --> 01:37:32.320
I have made a decision
regarding Sebastian's replacement.

1409
01:37:34.200 --> 01:37:37.120
And I want you to know
it wasn't an easy one.

1410
01:37:39.120 --> 01:37:43.440
This position brings with it
enormous responsibility

1411
01:37:43.520 --> 01:37:46.000
and my personal affection
for you aside...

1412
01:37:46.400 --> 01:37:50.480
I will have to go with
someone more, more experienced.

1413
01:38:48.400 --> 01:38:49.880
Oh, leave me alone.

1414
01:38:50.320 --> 01:38:51.840
I don't have your paper.

1415
01:38:52.920 --> 01:38:54.200
I've told you before, I...

1416
01:38:55.520 --> 01:38:57.000
Oh, I'm sorry. Please come in.

1417
01:39:41.760 --> 01:39:43.120
Good. Good.

1418
01:39:43.200 --> 01:39:45.800
I... I think the contrast is,
it's much better now.

1419
01:39:45.880 --> 01:39:46.920
Don't you think?

1420
01:39:47.800 --> 01:39:49.000
How do you take your coffee?

1421
01:39:49.240 --> 01:39:50.760
Black. Strong.

1422
01:39:53.160 --> 01:39:54.720
Is all right if I play?

1423
01:39:54.920 --> 01:39:56.560
Oh, yes, of course, of course.

1424
01:40:43.720 --> 01:40:45.000
That's as far as I've gotten.

1425
01:40:46.000 --> 01:40:47.120
But it's good.

1426
01:40:48.720 --> 01:40:49.920
This part here.

1427
01:40:54.240 --> 01:40:56.240
Maybe change A to B-flat?

1428
01:41:00.040 --> 01:41:01.680
That's better. I like that sound.

1429
01:41:04.000 --> 01:41:05.880
Come on. Take a break.

1430
01:41:05.960 --> 01:41:06.960
Okay.

1431
01:41:20.480 --> 01:41:21.480
Sharon?

1432
01:41:24.880 --> 01:41:25.880
Hello.

1433
01:41:41.720 --> 01:41:42.800
Petra.

1434
01:42:08.120 --> 01:42:09.560
What are you doing in here?

1435
01:42:09.920 --> 01:42:11.920
I'm hiding from her.

1436
01:42:13.080 --> 01:42:14.080
Why?

1437
01:42:14.280 --> 01:42:17.520
Because she told me
to put my things in order

1438
01:42:17.600 --> 01:42:19.520
but they already are.

1439
01:42:23.000 --> 01:42:24.200
I can see that.

1440
01:42:25.520 --> 01:42:26.560
Come on.

1441
01:42:27.120 --> 01:42:28.520
They're all waiting for you.

1442
01:42:29.160 --> 01:42:32.080
I'm going to give everyone a pencil.

1443
01:42:32.600 --> 01:42:34.880
All of them?
They can't all conduct, honey.

1444
01:42:34.960 --> 01:42:37.800
It's not a... it's not a democracy.

1445
01:43:41.720 --> 01:43:42.760
Okay.

1446
01:43:43.320 --> 01:43:46.720
Very nice. We'll go back
to the Allegro Molto after the break.

1447
01:43:47.640 --> 01:43:48.640
(German)

1448
01:43:48.920 --> 01:43:51.600
Hey, that's good. You happy?

1449
01:43:56.080 --> 01:43:58.640
How long were you
acquainted with Miss Taylor?

1450
01:43:59.120 --> 01:44:02.960
Oh, I'd have to double-check
with my assistant

1451
01:44:03.040 --> 01:44:06.760
but cumulatively speaking, I'd say
not more than a few months.

1452
01:44:08.160 --> 01:44:09.160
Thank you for your time

1453
01:44:09.240 --> 01:44:10.320
- Maestro.
- Not at all.

1454
01:44:11.680 --> 01:44:13.880
This recording will exist
on a protected server

1455
01:44:13.960 --> 01:44:16.240
under attorney-client
privilege with Mr. Singer.

1456
01:44:16.320 --> 01:44:17.656
- Great.
- He will follow up with you

1457
01:44:17.680 --> 01:44:19.200
to help prepare for the deposition.

1458
01:44:22.960 --> 01:44:23.960
Deposition?

1459
01:44:25.040 --> 01:44:26.040
Yes.

1460
01:44:26.200 --> 01:44:27.520
I assumed you were aware.

1461
01:44:28.320 --> 01:44:31.280
Mr. Singer's office said they'd been
coordinating with your assistant.

1462
01:44:32.000 --> 01:44:34.320
Francesca, you'd better get
your pretty little ass to work

1463
01:44:34.400 --> 01:44:35.440
right now.

1464
01:44:37.480 --> 01:44:39.520
The only communication
we've received from Francesca

1465
01:44:39.600 --> 01:44:41.736
was an email to my assistant
in the middle of the night

1466
01:44:41.760 --> 01:44:43.280
tendering her immediate resignation

1467
01:44:43.360 --> 01:44:46.600
stating she would be in contact
when she had more details to provide.

1468
01:44:47.600 --> 01:44:48.840
What kind of details?

1469
01:44:48.920 --> 01:44:50.520
A new address, I suppose.

1470
01:44:50.600 --> 01:44:52.520
In the meantime,
we've been trying all morning

1471
01:44:52.600 --> 01:44:55.040
to find someone suitable
to assist you on a temporary basis.

1472
01:44:55.120 --> 01:44:58.320
For now, perhaps your new assistant
conductor would be the right fit.

1473
01:44:58.400 --> 01:45:00.800
No. No. He's not available
'til after the live Five date.

1474
01:45:01.120 --> 01:45:02.440
Yes, I'm ready. Let's go.

1475
01:45:06.880 --> 01:45:08.640
I know how much you depended on her.

1476
01:45:08.720 --> 01:45:10.120
Two-faced little bitch.

1477
01:45:10.200 --> 01:45:11.480
Imagine her hurt, Tár.

1478
01:45:11.560 --> 01:45:13.640
- Don't you dare try to defend her.
- God, slow down!

1479
01:45:14.000 --> 01:45:16.880
She'll come galumphing back.
I mean, I've got a dumb phone

1480
01:45:16.960 --> 01:45:18.176
- like every robot. How hard
- Tár, s...

1481
01:45:18.200 --> 01:45:19.600
can it be to text all day?

1482
01:45:20.640 --> 01:45:22.080
Slow down!

1483
01:45:22.240 --> 01:45:23.360
Or let me out!

1484
01:45:44.120 --> 01:45:45.120
Francesca!

1485
01:46:18.320 --> 01:46:19.320
Fräulein?

1486
01:47:02.760 --> 01:47:05.200
(German)

1487
01:47:08.080 --> 01:47:09.080
Come.

1488
01:48:04.160 --> 01:48:05.520
(German)

1489
01:48:42.040 --> 01:48:43.520
Sorry I'm late again.

1490
01:48:50.200 --> 01:48:51.280
Do you live here?

1491
01:48:52.720 --> 01:48:54.000
Not normally, no.

1492
01:48:55.880 --> 01:48:57.936
Make yourself at home.
I'm just gonna put something on.

1493
01:48:57.960 --> 01:48:59.000
Do you have a towel?

1494
01:49:01.560 --> 01:49:02.760
- Yes.
- Thank you.

1495
01:49:08.440 --> 01:49:10.000
I got caught in the rain.

1496
01:49:21.960 --> 01:49:24.120
There is small concert
with musician friends.

1497
01:49:24.200 --> 01:49:25.240
You should come.

1498
01:49:26.600 --> 01:49:29.680
Thanks, but I...
really must get home.

1499
01:49:30.120 --> 01:49:31.360
You have child, yes?

1500
01:49:32.920 --> 01:49:34.000
I will not do that.

1501
01:49:36.920 --> 01:49:38.440
Pets are better for some people.

1502
01:49:50.920 --> 01:49:51.920
What... Oh.

1503
01:49:52.440 --> 01:49:53.520
- Sorry.
- Bye.

1504
01:49:53.600 --> 01:49:54.720
Oh, yes. Goodbye. Yes.

1505
01:49:54.800 --> 01:49:55.840
- Goodbye.
- Okay.

1506
01:49:56.160 --> 01:49:57.680
- Oh.
- Okay.

1507
01:50:04.440 --> 01:50:05.480
Oh, Olga!

1508
01:50:06.240 --> 01:50:07.240
Olga!

1509
01:50:15.000 --> 01:50:16.000
Olga?

1510
01:50:23.200 --> 01:50:24.320
Olga?

1511
01:50:52.240 --> 01:50:53.240
Hello?

1512
01:51:05.280 --> 01:51:06.280
Olga?

1513
01:51:24.760 --> 01:51:25.880
Olga?

1514
01:51:35.120 --> 01:51:36.200
Olga?

1515
01:52:22.040 --> 01:52:23.800
Why didn't you go to the police?

1516
01:52:24.160 --> 01:52:26.520
I fought. He ran. What's to tell?

1517
01:52:30.360 --> 01:52:32.640
Oh, God. I'm gonna get you
something for the pain.

1518
01:52:32.720 --> 01:52:35.200
- No, I don't need anything.
- No, I'm gonna get you something.

1519
01:52:41.520 --> 01:52:42.520
<i>Ja.</i>

1520
01:52:58.160 --> 01:53:00.000
Lydia!

1521
01:53:03.280 --> 01:53:04.760
Lydia!

1522
01:53:09.560 --> 01:53:10.560
What is it?

1523
01:53:13.400 --> 01:53:14.920
Hold my foot.

1524
01:53:23.200 --> 01:53:24.200
Is that better?

1525
01:53:24.760 --> 01:53:25.760
Yes.

1526
01:54:05.800 --> 01:54:06.800
Okay.

1527
01:54:07.840 --> 01:54:09.800
Let's shoo the elephant
from the room.

1528
01:54:11.400 --> 01:54:12.920
"What the hell happened to her face?"

1529
01:54:13.960 --> 01:54:16.480
"Did she schedule a nose and eye job

1530
01:54:16.560 --> 01:54:18.720
and bail before the surgeon
finished the other half?"

1531
01:54:24.200 --> 01:54:25.200
No.

1532
01:54:25.720 --> 01:54:27.480
I was... I was attacked.

1533
01:54:28.120 --> 01:54:29.160
Thank you.

1534
01:54:29.920 --> 01:54:31.400
I'm fine. Really.

1535
01:54:31.920 --> 01:54:33.080
Should've seen the other guy.

1536
01:54:33.440 --> 01:54:34.440
All right.

1537
01:54:34.520 --> 01:54:39.720
Second movement, let's take
the transition Bar 406.

1538
01:55:18.040 --> 01:55:20.000
Don't. It burns.

1539
01:55:21.000 --> 01:55:22.520
You must see the doctor.

1540
01:55:23.080 --> 01:55:24.760
He's booked 'til next week.

1541
01:55:25.400 --> 01:55:26.616
I'll call them again and tell them

1542
01:55:26.640 --> 01:55:28.176
- how much pain you're in.
- No, no, let's just...

1543
01:55:28.200 --> 01:55:29.320
let's just finish up here.

1544
01:55:30.320 --> 01:55:31.320
Okay?

1545
01:55:31.720 --> 01:55:33.680
