02:17:26.440 --> 02:17:28.880
you want to show Lydia
what you've prepared for her?

1797
02:17:28.960 --> 02:17:30.000
Well...

1798
02:17:31.360 --> 02:17:33.200
right now it's a reset.

1799
02:17:33.760 --> 02:17:35.200
What we're after is less, not more.

1800
02:17:35.280 --> 02:17:38.520
We want to be selective
and rebuild this from the ground up.

1801
02:17:38.600 --> 02:17:40.200
That means we need a new story.

1802
02:17:44.720 --> 02:17:45.720
Just here.

1803
02:17:46.480 --> 02:17:47.560
Here. Thank you.

1804
02:17:48.720 --> 02:17:49.720
Make it 40.

1805
02:17:50.000 --> 02:17:51.000
Thank you.

1806
02:19:21.440 --> 02:19:23.000
<i>Didn't you feel triumphant?</i>

1807
02:19:26.800 --> 02:19:30.200
<i>Now we can really understand
what the meaning of music is.</i>

1808
02:19:30.520 --> 02:19:34.000
<i>It's the way it makes you feel
when you hear it.</i>

1809
02:19:34.920 --> 02:19:37.000
<i>Finally, we've taken
that last giant step.</i>

1810
02:19:37.080 --> 02:19:39.720
<i>And we're there.
We know what music means now.</i>

1811
02:19:39.960 --> 02:19:42.240
<i>And we don't have to know
a lot of stuff about sharps</i>

1812
02:19:42.320 --> 02:19:45.000
<i>and flats and chords
and all that business</i>

1813
02:19:45.240 --> 02:19:48.920
<i>in order to understand music
if it tells us something.</i>

1814
02:19:49.760 --> 02:19:53.080
<i>And the most wonderful thing of all
is that there's no limit</i>

1815
02:19:53.160 --> 02:19:56.640
<i>to the different kinds of feelings
music can make you have.</i>

1816
02:19:57.200 --> 02:20:00.760
<i>And some of those feelings
are so special and so deep</i>

1817
02:20:00.840 --> 02:20:03.120
<i>that they can't even
be described in words.</i>

1818
02:20:03.520 --> 02:20:05.680
<i>You see, we can't always name
the things we feel.</i>

1819
02:20:05.760 --> 02:20:08.240
<i>Sometimes we can.
We can say we feel joy</i>

1820
02:20:08.440 --> 02:20:11.400
<i>pleasure, peacefulness,
whatever, love, hate.</i>

1821
02:20:12.000 --> 02:20:14.040
<i>But every once in a while</i>

1822
02:20:14.240 --> 02:20:16.920
<i>we have feelings that are
so deep and so special</i>

1823
02:20:17.200 --> 02:20:18.480
<i>that we have no words for them.</i>

1824
02:20:18.560 --> 02:20:21.360
<i>And that's where
music is so marvelous</i>

1825
02:20:21.440 --> 02:20:26.280
<i>because music names them for us,
only in notes instead of in words.</i>

1826
02:20:26.520 --> 02:20:28.080
<i>It's all in the way music moves.</i>

1827
02:20:28.160 --> 02:20:30.600
<i>You must never forget
that music is movement</i>

1828
02:20:30.680 --> 02:20:33.320
<i>always going somewhere,
shifting and changing</i>

1829
02:20:33.400 --> 02:20:36.600
<i>and flowing from one note to another.</i>

1830
02:20:36.680 --> 02:20:38.000
<i>And that movement can tell us</i>

1831
02:20:38.080 --> 02:20:41.200
<i>more about the way we feel
than a million words can.</i>

1832
02:20:41.680 --> 02:20:43.240
<i>And here we're going to play you a...</i>

1833
02:20:57.120 --> 02:20:58.120
Tony.

1834
02:20:59.760 --> 02:21:00.760
Oh.

1835
02:21:01.400 --> 02:21:02.400
Hi, Linda.

1836
02:21:02.640 --> 02:21:03.640
Sorry.

1837
02:21:03.840 --> 02:21:04.840
Lydia.

1838
02:21:06.080 --> 02:21:07.520
Ma said you'd be over.

1839
02:21:08.400 --> 02:21:09.760
You must be hiding out.

1840
02:21:11.440 --> 02:21:12.880
Why would I be hiding out?

1841
02:21:13.880 --> 02:21:15.200
Beats the hell out of me.

1842
02:21:16.040 --> 02:21:17.560
None of my business anyhow.

1843
02:21:19.360 --> 02:21:21.160
Lot of loose ends, you got to admit.

1844
02:21:23.160 --> 02:21:24.200
What do you mean?

1845
02:21:24.680 --> 02:21:26.480
Well, like I said,
it ain't my business.

1846
02:21:28.400 --> 02:21:30.056
But you don't seem to know
where the hell you came from

1847
02:21:30.080 --> 02:21:31.120
or where you're going.

1848
02:22:21.840 --> 02:22:23.000
May I come inside?

1849
02:22:25.000 --> 02:22:26.000
Thank you.

1850
02:22:38.240 --> 02:22:39.480
I'm so sorry.

1851
02:22:39.560 --> 02:22:42.120
We just wanted to confirm
that the composer was in fact

1852
02:22:42.200 --> 02:22:44.560
not flying in from Osaka
to attend the concert.

1853
02:22:45.400 --> 02:22:48.760
I... I must tell you that
I... I looked in the music libraries

1854
02:22:49.040 --> 02:22:51.880
for her score,
but I... I couldn't find anything.

1855
02:22:52.240 --> 02:22:53.480
This just arrived.

1856
02:22:54.400 --> 02:22:55.640
That's great. Thank you.

1857
02:22:57.920 --> 02:23:00.760
Shirley and Cirio will be most happy
to show you the sights

1858
02:23:00.840 --> 02:23:02.016
- of our beautiful country.
- Thank you.

1859
02:23:02.040 --> 02:23:03.240
Thank you so much.

1860
02:23:03.920 --> 02:23:05.040
Oh, goodness.

1861
02:23:06.000 --> 02:23:07.120
Thank... thank you.

1862
02:23:37.680 --> 02:23:40.520
Maybe we could stop somewhere
and take a swim.

1863
02:23:41.520 --> 02:23:43.120
Yeah, at the waterfall.

1864
02:23:43.200 --> 02:23:45.120
But not in the river.

1865
02:23:45.200 --> 02:23:47.240
Why? Is there something wrong
with the water?

1866
02:23:47.640 --> 02:23:49.640
No. There are crocodiles.

1867
02:23:50.160 --> 02:23:51.160
Oh.

1868
02:23:52.440 --> 02:23:54.200
I didn't think
they'd be this far inland.

1869
02:23:54.720 --> 02:23:56.920
They escaped from
Marlon Brando movie.

1870
02:23:57.480 --> 02:23:58.480
Wow.

1871
02:23:59.200 --> 02:24:00.880
That was a long time ago.

1872
02:24:01.920 --> 02:24:03.000
They survive.

1873
02:24:36.720 --> 02:24:38.360
Lady. Lady.

1874
02:24:40.800 --> 02:24:42.200
Here is prescription.

1875
02:24:42.280 --> 02:24:43.800
- Ten dollars.
- Oh. Thank you.

1876
02:24:45.800 --> 02:24:48.960
Is there somewhere
around here... Thank you.

1877
02:24:49.240 --> 02:24:50.720
Where I could get a massage?

1878
02:24:51.240 --> 02:24:54.040
Was hoping it might help me
with this jet lag.

1879
02:24:57.600 --> 02:24:58.640
Yes.

1880
02:24:58.840 --> 02:25:00.880
There is the very nice place I know.

1881
02:25:01.400 --> 02:25:02.400
Thank you.

1882
02:25:15.760 --> 02:25:16.760
Thank you.

1883
02:25:16.840 --> 02:25:18.360
Please step over to the fishbowl.

1884
02:25:18.720 --> 02:25:20.200
The... the fishbowl?

1885
02:25:20.480 --> 02:25:21.560
Yes, over there.

1886
02:25:28.080 --> 02:25:30.600
I'm sorry, I'm confused.
