1887
02:25:31.800 --> 02:25:33.200
You just pick a number here.

1888
02:25:35.640 --> 02:25:37.080
I pick a number?

1889
02:25:37.160 --> 02:25:38.160
Yes.

1890
02:25:49.760 --> 02:25:50.880
Number five?

1891
02:26:33.160 --> 02:26:34.160
Good morning.

1892
02:26:34.440 --> 02:26:35.640
Good morning.

1893
02:26:35.800 --> 02:26:38.360
Now, before we begin,
let's... let's talk a bit

1894
02:26:38.440 --> 02:26:41.800
about the composer's intent
with this piece.

1895
02:26:43.320 --> 02:26:44.680
And what she might be after.

1896
02:27:03.400 --> 02:27:04.600
Five minutes.

1897
02:27:35.600 --> 02:27:36.600
Thank you.

1898
02:28:00.480 --> 02:28:04.000
<i>Sisters and brothers
of the Fifth Fleet, it's time.</i>

1899
02:28:04.600 --> 02:28:06.520
<i>I'll keep my farewell brief.</i>

1900
02:28:06.720 --> 02:28:08.400
<i>Never was much with words.</i>

1901
02:28:09.280 --> 02:28:12.600
<i>Once you board this ship,
there's no turning back.</i>

1902
02:28:13.320 --> 02:28:17.320
<i>The next ground your feet touch
